Test Plan – Swag Labs

Objective

Validate the main functionalities of the Swag Labs application through functional and exploratory testing, ensuring that the main user flows work as expected.

Scope

The following features will be covered during testing:

- User authentication (Login)
- Product listing and product details
- Shopping cart management
- Checkout process

Out of Scope

The following types of testing are not included in this test cycle:

- Performance testing
- Security testing
- Cross-browser compatibility testing

Test Types

The following testing types will be performed:

- Functional Testing
- Exploratory Testing
- Positive Testing
- Negative Testing

Test Environment

Application: Swag Labs (SauceDemo)
Browser: Google Chrome
Operating System: Windows

Test Data

The following test data will be used:

- Valid user credentials
- Invalid user credentials
- Empty fields
- Product information
- Checkout information

Test Tools

The following tools will be used during testing:

- Google Chrome
- GitHub
- Markdown
- Microsoft Excel / Google Sheets

Test Approach

Testing will focus on validating the main user journeys:

1. User authentication.
2. Product selection and management.
3. Adding and removing products from the shopping cart.
4. Completing the checkout process.

Both positive and negative scenarios will be executed to validate system behavior and identify possible defects.

Risks

The following risks were identified:

- Login failures may prevent users from accessing the application.
- Shopping cart failures may prevent users from adding or removing products.
- Checkout failures may prevent users from completing purchases.

Entry Criteria

Testing can start when:

- The application is available.
- Test scenarios and requirements are defined.
- The test environment is configured.

Exit Criteria

Testing will be considered completed when:

- All planned test cases have been executed.
- Test results have been documented.
- Identified defects have been reported.
